<h2>Tables</h2>
<article class="element-copy">
  <p>Check out <a href="https://github.com/o2Labs/White-Paper/blob/master/source/assets/stylesheets/sass/_tables.scss">_tables.scss</a> for all the styles.</p>
	<p>Hoping more extensive tables will be added as we go on (eg. collapsable & sortable), for the minute we have a basic table and a simple table.</p>
	<section class="element-one">
		<table summary="An example of a basic table">
      <caption>Basic table: This is the <code>caption</code></caption>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Headings</th><th>are wrapped</th><th>in <code>thead</code> with <code>th</code> cells</th>
</tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><th>Here are</th><td>Some main</td><td>data cells (<code>td</code>)</td></tr>
        <tr><th>These are all</th><td>Wrapped in the</td><td><code>tbody</code> element</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Tables</th><td>Can get very</td><td>Confusing</td></tr>
        <tr><th>They are also a</th><td>Complete bitch</td><td>To syle</td></tr>
      </tbody>
      <tfoot>
        <tr><td>I have also</td><td>Included a <code>tfoot</code></td><td>Just cos</td></tr>
      </tfoot>
  	</table>
